text.tspan: To colorize a custom test design that you want on the grid (you will need to create all new settigns files, ie 200 new settings, manually.):
1. Put design into the first position on the grid. UNSET THE FILL/STROKE COLORS!
3. Show design layer on top of colorizer layer
5. Shift tab. If the design is 6x4mm: shift-x, per column = 33.333%; shift-y, per row = 40%. If not, see below
8. Choose Width, Height at the bottom and set it to the overall grid w/h
9. Create, then hide the colorizer layer.
If the spacing is off, you'll need to change the shift values in the shift tab.
Take your design dimensions and the spacing between grid areas and calculate:
x per col% = ((sx - dx)/dx) * 100 <== and the same for y per row using y-values
